WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:04.136
Okay, Rock Paper Scissors.

00:04.138 --> 00:06.538
Loser has to ask the guy
in gym shorts at table 12

00:06.540 --> 00:09.508
to stop Sharon Stoneing us
his balls.

00:14.948 --> 00:17.449
By virtue of having
this conversation,

00:17.451 --> 00:19.385
aren't we both losers?

00:19.387 --> 00:22.321
Look who's back from Hollywood.

00:22.323 --> 00:25.224
If it isn't ScarJo and J-Lo.

00:25.226 --> 00:28.093
Said the guy from down low.

00:28.095 --> 00:29.928
Can I get an autograph?

00:29.930 --> 00:33.932
Oops, my bad--
still just waitresses.

00:33.934 --> 00:39.304
Han, don't be upset just because
I'm about to make $250,000

00:39.306 --> 00:40.939
and have a movie made
about me.

00:40.941 --> 00:43.409
Han already had
a movie made about him--

00:43.411 --> 00:45.677
"Paul Blart: Small Cop."

00:47.047 --> 00:51.417
What's your movie called?
"Straight Outta A Job"?

00:52.819 --> 00:55.154
<i>(Peter Bjorn and John)</i>
<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh</i>

00:55.156 --> 00:56.555
<i>[cash register bell dings]</i>

00:56.557 --> 01:00.459
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh

01:02.695 --> 01:04.930
Yeah, about that?
You can't fire us now.

01:04.932 --> 01:06.465
The money hasn't come in
just yet.

01:06.467 --> 01:09.334
After that, by all means,
please fire us

01:09.336 --> 01:10.936
and fire us hard.

01:10.938 --> 01:14.773
Yeah, how does firing us
on the 27th work for you?

01:14.775 --> 01:16.642
Don't think I won't do it.

01:16.644 --> 01:20.179
I've been wanting another Asian
in the mix for some time.

01:20.181 --> 01:23.115
Oh, and, Han, we're gonna need
the day off tomorrow.

01:23.117 --> 01:25.551
You just took ten days off!

01:25.553 --> 01:27.486
No more vacation days.

01:27.488 --> 01:29.822
Freddie Prinze Jr. works
more than you two.

01:29.824 --> 01:33.525
Max and I are going to prison
to visit my dad.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.394
As part of his therapy,
he's written a musical,

01:35.396 --> 01:37.563
and he's performing it
with the other inmates.

01:37.565 --> 01:39.832
A musical in prison?

01:39.834 --> 01:42.367
I'd be shaking my damn head
right now

01:42.369 --> 01:45.137
if my neck still worked.

01:45.139 --> 01:49.041
And, again, you can fire us
on the 27th.

01:49.043 --> 01:50.476
We're in flux now.

01:50.478 --> 01:54.012
And as always, I'm the one
who gets fluxed.

01:55.982 --> 01:57.950
Aw, I missed Han.

01:57.952 --> 02:01.353
I've never heard you say that
without a crossbow in your hand.

02:01.355 --> 02:03.555
I can't wait
till we get that money.

02:03.557 --> 02:04.857
Think of all the stuff
we could buy.

02:04.859 --> 02:07.526
[gasps]
American toothpaste.

02:07.528 --> 02:11.864
Some toilet paper so we can
stop using our bath mat.

02:11.866 --> 02:13.665
And since we're unfreezing
our credit card,

02:13.667 --> 02:15.234
maybe I'll get
a new dress too.

02:15.236 --> 02:18.003
The invite to this musical
said "cocktail attire."

02:18.005 --> 02:21.173
A prison musical
with cocktail attire?

02:21.175 --> 02:22.608
Ah, screw it.

02:22.610 --> 02:28.213
I'm gonna feel this tomorrow,
but mm, mm!

02:28.215 --> 02:30.215
Mm!

02:30.217 --> 02:32.050
Hey, everybody!

02:33.953 --> 02:36.021
Today's the day
Oleg and me find out

02:36.023 --> 02:39.858
what kind of sex
our baby's gonna have.

02:39.860 --> 02:42.661
I beg you to rephrase that.

02:42.663 --> 02:44.730
(Oleg)
Baby, I don't want to know

02:44.732 --> 02:46.498
if it's gonna be a boy
or a girl.

02:46.500 --> 02:47.966
I'd rather be surprised.

02:47.968 --> 02:51.203
You know, like when you get
a hooker in Tijuana.

02:51.205 --> 02:53.672
Boy, do I.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.474
Or girl, do I.

02:55.476 --> 02:59.211
Oh! We don't know,
and that's the fun.

02:59.213 --> 03:00.846
(Oleg)
We're gonna have a baker

03:00.848 --> 03:03.649
do one of those gender reveal
cakes for us.

03:03.651 --> 03:05.817
Can you guys recommend
a baker?

03:07.287 --> 03:09.188
Uh, excuse me?

03:09.190 --> 03:11.490
Yeah, excuse me?

03:11.492 --> 03:14.026
What the hell
is a gender reveal cake?

03:14.028 --> 03:17.696
Like, you bake it and then
you pull its pants down?

03:17.698 --> 03:19.298
Jeez, would it kill you

03:19.300 --> 03:22.834
to pick up a "Rachael Ray
Every Day" once in a while?

03:22.836 --> 03:26.505
We give the bakers a sealed
envelope with the sex.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.040
Yeah, and then the bakers--

03:28.042 --> 03:31.176
you know, if we can find
good ones--

03:31.178 --> 03:34.213
will make the icing
on the inside pink

03:34.215 --> 03:35.681
if it's a Svetlana...

03:35.683 --> 03:38.684
And blue if it's a Svetlenny.

03:38.686 --> 03:41.220
Well, it beats the way
they did it

03:41.222 --> 03:42.554
in my town in Poland.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.523
You were either a boy

03:44.525 --> 03:48.026
or you had to know how to climb
back up out of a well.

03:48.028 --> 03:49.962
Yeah.

03:49.964 --> 03:53.298
Um, you know
we're bakers, right?

03:53.300 --> 03:54.766
Hell, yeah.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.268
I'm baked right now.

04:03.910 --> 04:07.279
Well, I'm dressed for
my father's prison musical.

04:07.281 --> 04:08.280
[sighs]

04:08.282 --> 04:11.717
Say that three times
without crying.

04:11.719 --> 04:13.252
You look good.

04:13.254 --> 04:15.354
If those inmates weren't
hardened criminals before,

04:15.356 --> 04:17.889
they will be
once they see you in that.

04:17.891 --> 04:20.359
What's with all
the miniature liquor bottles

04:20.361 --> 04:21.760
you stole from the plane?

04:21.762 --> 04:25.197
Do I have to host
a tiny intervention?

04:25.199 --> 04:27.232
I did not steal these
from the plane.

04:27.234 --> 04:28.967
I stole them
from our hotel room,

04:28.969 --> 04:30.969
the maid cart, and a few
other people's hotel rooms

04:30.971 --> 04:32.337
when I posed as a maid.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.073
This is part
of my presentation

04:35.075 --> 04:38.076
for my idea on how to spend
the $250,000.

04:38.078 --> 04:40.612
Five years ago,
we were sitting on Chestnut

04:40.614 --> 04:41.880
with our iced coffees.

04:41.882 --> 04:44.650
I remember it
like it was five years ago.

04:44.652 --> 04:47.786
And we said that $250,000

04:47.788 --> 04:49.655
the exact amount
of money we're getting,

04:49.657 --> 04:52.291
was what we needed to get
our cupcake business going.

04:52.293 --> 04:54.693
Chestnut was so excited,
he made a little poo.

04:54.695 --> 04:56.328
[Chestnut chuffs]

04:56.330 --> 04:57.496
Not so little.

04:57.498 --> 05:01.400
I remember it knocking
that cat unconscious.

05:01.402 --> 05:02.701
Five years later,

05:02.703 --> 05:04.803
cupcakes alone
aren't cutting it.

05:04.805 --> 05:06.405
Ouch.
But true.

05:06.407 --> 05:09.341
Sure, they're sweet,
delicious, and chic,

05:09.343 --> 05:13.211
but what if we add...
alcohol?

05:13.213 --> 05:17.316
Which is sweet, delicious,
and expensive?

05:18.751 --> 05:20.852
We keep the cupcake window,

05:20.854 --> 05:23.855
but we make it
into a bar too.

05:23.857 --> 05:26.958
It's two great things
put together!

05:26.960 --> 05:28.460
Like you and me?

05:28.462 --> 05:30.462
I was gonna say
fat people and tripping,

05:30.464 --> 05:32.230
but yes!

05:32.232 --> 05:34.399
We keep the cupcake dream;

05:34.401 --> 05:37.469
we just add
overpriced alcohol to it.

05:37.471 --> 05:38.537
I love it!

05:38.539 --> 05:41.073
We can call it
Cupcakes & Cocktails.

05:41.075 --> 05:43.442
Or, if we want to be
less douchey,

05:43.444 --> 05:46.011
we call it Dessert Bar.

05:46.013 --> 05:48.580
That is a genius idea.

05:48.582 --> 05:50.582
Usually when you're drunk,
your best idea is,

05:50.584 --> 05:53.518
"Let's call Home Depot
and ask if they have caulk."

05:54.954 --> 05:56.755
So we're doing it?

05:56.757 --> 05:58.123
We're opening up
a dessert bar?

05:58.125 --> 06:00.592
Oh, we're opening up
a dessert bar.

06:00.594 --> 06:01.927
Celebratory dance?

06:04.964 --> 06:06.765
Am I here yet?

06:06.767 --> 06:08.266
[sniffing]

06:08.268 --> 06:10.969
I know I'm either
at Max and Caroline's

06:10.971 --> 06:13.138
or a petting zoo.

06:13.140 --> 06:16.775
To be clear, that horse smell
is the couch.

06:16.777 --> 06:19.311
Oh, I just came back
from the doctor,

06:19.313 --> 06:22.481
and I have the sex of the baby,
but I don't want to see it.

06:22.483 --> 06:26.084
So please take it from me quick
so I don't sneak a peek.

06:28.354 --> 06:29.488
(Max)
Caroline,

06:29.490 --> 06:30.822
you hold on to this

06:30.824 --> 06:32.090
until it's time
to bake the cake.

06:32.092 --> 06:33.525
(Sophie)
Why are you giving it
to her?

06:33.527 --> 06:35.327
I mean, you really think
she can keep a secret

06:35.329 --> 06:38.997
with that big Jim Carrey mouth
flapping all the time?

06:40.466 --> 06:42.701
Well, you don't want me
to have it.

06:42.703 --> 06:44.002
If I know, I'll spoil it.

06:44.004 --> 06:45.404
I have no poker face.

06:45.406 --> 06:47.472
Neither did my mom,
which is how I became

06:47.474 --> 06:51.009
the legal property
of the Borgata Casino.

06:51.011 --> 06:53.178
Caroline, I'm warning you.

06:53.180 --> 06:55.313
Don't let it slip.

06:55.315 --> 06:59.251
Even if I beg you,
don't tell me.

06:59.253 --> 07:00.485
Okay.

07:00.487 --> 07:02.988
Even if I come downstairs
in the middle of the night

07:02.990 --> 07:05.524
and put a gun to your head,

07:05.526 --> 07:07.926
don't tell me.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.995
Okay, well,
if there's a gun involved,

07:09.997 --> 07:11.062
I'm gonna tell you.

07:11.064 --> 07:12.564
See, Max?

07:12.566 --> 07:14.232
That's why I didn't want
to give it to her.

07:23.176 --> 07:26.244
Your dad wrote and directed
this thing too?

07:26.246 --> 07:29.114
Dang, he's like
the Ben Affleck of jail.

07:29.116 --> 07:31.082
Yikes, it says here

07:31.084 --> 07:32.951
that the guy who was playing
"sadistic guard"

07:32.953 --> 07:34.453
is out
for tonight's performance

07:34.455 --> 07:37.189
because someone took his eye out
with a plastic spork.

07:37.191 --> 07:39.758
Oh, my God.
That's terrible.

07:39.760 --> 07:42.861
We're seeing an understudy?

07:42.863 --> 07:45.597
Oh, look!
My dad's opening the show.

07:45.599 --> 07:48.733
[piano introduction plays]

07:48.735 --> 07:52.804
♪ Steel bars

07:52.806 --> 07:56.208
♪ Steel bars on my heart

07:56.210 --> 07:58.810
♪ Steels bars on my soul

07:58.812 --> 08:00.278
♪ And there's no parole

08:00.280 --> 08:03.715
♪ And it tears me apart

08:03.717 --> 08:08.119
all: ♪ Steel bars

08:08.121 --> 08:11.790
♪ Steel bars on our balls

08:11.792 --> 08:14.025
♪ Steel bars on this jail

08:14.027 --> 08:16.027
♪ And there ain't no bail

08:16.029 --> 08:20.165
♪ And nobody calls

08:20.167 --> 08:23.134
I call him twice a week.

08:23.136 --> 08:25.837
all: ♪ Steel bars
on our balls ♪

08:25.839 --> 08:28.974
♪ Steel bars on our balls

08:28.976 --> 08:31.843
♪ Steel bars
